# Absences

## Access

Accessible by all authenticated users.

## Overview

The Absences page allows employees to submit, track, and manage absence requests. Admins can review (approve or reject) any absence.

## Absence types

- Vacation
- Sick Leave
- Personal
- Unpaid
- Maternity
- Paternity
- Bereavement
- Study
- Time in Lieu

## Business rules

### Vacation allowance

- Each employee has an annual vacation day allowance (default: 25 days).
- The balance resets each calendar year.
- The balance panel shows: allowance / used / pending / remaining days.

### Time in Lieu

- An employee can only request a Time in Lieu absence if they have an **approved** TIL record in the database.
- When submitting, the employee selects which TIL record to apply from a dropdown.
- On approval the TIL record is marked as **used**; if the absence is subsequently rejected the TIL record is restored to **approved**.

### Editing

- A **pending** absence may be edited by the employee who submitted it.
- Once **approved** or **rejected** the absence is read-only for employees.
- An admin may re-review (approve → reject or reject → approve) an absence at any time.

### Overlap prevention

- Two non-cancelled/non-rejected absences for the same employee cannot overlap in date range.
- This is enforced both on the frontend (UI warning) and on the backend (409 conflict response).

### Working day calculation

- `totalDays` counts only working days (Monday–Friday).
- Weekends and bank/public/company holidays are excluded from the count.
